draw((5,5)--(11,10),dashed);
draw((2,3)--(2,5)--(13,5)--(13,8)--cycle,gray(.7));
draw((2,3)--(2,10),dashed);
draw((13,5)--(13,10),dashed);
label("$d$",(8,5),S);
label("$y$",(13,6.5),E);
[/asy]

The rectangle has width $d = \frac{|3y - x - 15|}{\sqrt{10}}$ and height $dy$, so its area is $\frac{|3y - x - 15|}{\sqrt{10}} \cdot dy$. We need to integrate this area from $y = \frac{1}{3}x + 5$ to $y = x - 2$, and then double the result.

\begin{align*}
V &= 2\int_4^{13} \int_{\frac{1}{3}x + 5}^{x - 2} \frac{|3y - x - 15|}{\sqrt{10}} \cdot dy \, dx \\
&= 2\int_4^{13} \int_{\frac{1}{3}x + 5}^{\frac{x+15}{3}} \frac{(3y - x - 15)}{\sqrt{10}} \cdot dy \, dx + 2\int_4^{13} \int_{\frac{x+15}{3}}^{x-2} \frac{(x + 15 - 3y)}{\sqrt{10}} \cdot dy \, dx \\
&= 2\int_4^{13} \left[ \frac{3}{2\sqrt{10}} y^2 - \frac{1}{\sqrt{10}} xy - \frac{15}{2\sqrt{10}} y \right]_{y=\frac{1}{3}x+5}^{y=\frac{x+15}{3}} \, dx \\
&\quad + 2\int_4^{13} \left[ \frac{1}{2\sqrt{10}} xy - \frac{3}{2\sqrt{10}} y^2 + \frac{15}{\sqrt{10}} y \right]_{y=\frac{x+15}{3}}^{y=x-2} \, dx \\
&= 2\int_4^{13} \left( \frac{2x^2 - 2x - 19}{6\sqrt{10}} \right) \, dx + 2\int_4^{13} \left( \frac{2x^2 - 58x + 344}{18\sqrt{10}} \right) \, dx \\
&= \frac{22\pi}{\sqrt{10}},
\end{align*}where we used the fact that the integral of an odd function over a symmetric interval is 0 to simplify the double integral. Thus, $m + n + p = 22 + 10 + 10 = \boxed{042}$.

