If $X$ is a $60$-ray partitional point, then the angle between adjacent rays is $120^{\circ}.$  We claim that there is no $60$-ray partitional point in the interior of the square.

Suppose there exists a $60$-ray partitional point $X$ in the interior of the square.  Let $A,$ $B,$ and $C$ be the points of intersection of three adjacent rays with the square.

