Since $X$ is $60$-ray partitional, the triangles $AXB,$ $BXC,$ and $CXD$ all have the same area.  But triangle $AXB$ is a $30^\circ$-$60^\circ$-$90^\circ$ triangle, so the ratio of its legs is $1:\sqrt{3}.$  Therefore, the ratio of the heights of triangles $AXB$ and $BXC$ is $\sqrt{3}:1.$  Since these triangles have the same area, triangle $BXC$ is also a $30^\circ$-$60^\circ$-$90^\circ$ triangle.  Similarly, triangle $CXA$ is a $30^\circ$-$60^\circ$-$90^\circ$ triangle.

